    <p>Ten thousand dead <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="made"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(等于/合计为)</code></b> about five times the audience in a biggish cinema.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But, again, in the Canton epidemic there was no reliable way of counting up the rats. A very rough estimate was all that could be made, with, obviously, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="a wide margin for error"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(很容易出差错)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>He <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="pulled himself up - (pull up - 制止)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(让自己停止)</code></b> sharply. He was letting his imagination <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="play pranks"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(恶作剧，引申为任凭自己天马行空地想象)</code></b>—the last thing wanted just now. A few cases, he told himself, don’t make an epidemic; they merely call for serious precautions.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And, gazing in the direction of the bay, Dr. Rieux <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="called to mind"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(使回忆起某事)</code></b> the plague-fires of which Lucremoutius tells, which the Anthenians kindled on the seashore.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Rieux <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="pulled himself together"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(重新振作起来)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And since a dead man <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="has no substance"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(无足轻重)</code></b> unless one has actually seen him dead, a hundred million corposes broadcast through history are no more than <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="a puff of smoke"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(一缕青烟)</code></b> in the imagination.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Yes, in conclusion, the patient’s life <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="hung on a thread"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(命悬一线)</code></b>, and three people out of four (he remembered the exact figures) were too impatient not to make the very slight movement that <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="snapped the thread"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(啪地一声折断)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The doctor was still looking out of the window. Beyond it lay <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the tranquil radiance of a cool spring sky"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(凉爽的春天天空的宁静光辉)</code></b>; inside the room a word was echoing still, the word “plague.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Only the sea, murmurous behind the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="DIRTY, UNCLEAN"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">dingy</code></b> checkerboard of houses, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="told of"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(述说着)</code></b> the unrest, the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="\ pri-ˈker-ē-əs-nəs \ precarious - dependent on chance circumstances, unknown conditions, or uncertain developments"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">precariousness</code></b>, of all things in this world.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But these extravagant forebodings dwindled in the light of reason. True, the word “plague” had been uttered; true, at this very moment one or two victims were being seized and <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="laid low"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(倒下/平卧)</code></b> by the disease.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Then the plague would come to an end, because it was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="being contrary to what is reasonable, desirable, or probable - being out of the question"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">unthinkable</code></b>, or, rather, because one <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="thought of it on misleading lines"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(在误导人的基础上进行思考)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>There lay <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="\ ˈsər-tə-ˌtüd \ the state of being or feeling certain"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">certitude</code></b>; there, in the daily round. All the rest hung on mere threads and trivial contingencies; you couldn’t waste your time on it. The thing was to do your job as it should be done.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
